column5: Hi all, still around 2 foot of fairly decent ice, walleyes get a break for a bit, but crappies are still fair game! Better get out today as well before we get hit by the winter storm tomorrow. VIDEO LINKhttps://youtu.be/kWz9w2HRrFQ
Crappieâ€™s are a lot of fun especially in cold water, great video!
They are also great tasting fish coming out of cold water !
Nice video. Crappie are a favorite of mine also.
Are you over a brush pile down there, or just natural structure? I'm not sure I have the constitution to be out ice fishing, but it is fun to watch :-)
The crappie congregate in the deep basins here on wabigoon lake during winter, mud flats normally but the spot I was fishing was on a steep rock face where it meets mud.
